Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the blue line ALWAYS gets back to the green, as it is just a 24 hour average. it usually crosses at an angle, that is why the prior pattern of soft landing in the green line and then stair stepping stood out as strange

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: after the stairstepping stopped, we seem to be oscillating, so normal TA should be able be decently accurate (until the stairmaster starts again)

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the thing about trading signals is that if you want something that is always telling you up vs down, it wont be very accurate well in forex i got one to get to 85% accurate for 2 hours ahead, but it is hard to make money with that as the magnitude of movement is not that big

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so try to make predictors that predict the big moves and dont bother with the small stuff as you will just overtrade and lose all your profits
